# Development Workflow

## Pre-Change Check
1. Read ui-memory.mdc for existing fixes
2. Never revert documented solutions

## Guidelines  
- prefer code comments
- Don't create extraneous files
- Show code chunks, not descriptions

## Workflow
1. Memory check (ui-memory.mdc)
2. Run/refresh app (`./dev`)
3. Test changes
4. Commit if accepted

## After Acceptance
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Brief description"
git push origin main
```

## Development Server
```bash
./dev          # Standard with live reload
./dev-debug    # Maximum error visibility
```

## Memory Preservation
- Document-driven development prevents AI amnesia
- Update .mdc files for recurring issues
